  "text": "and RRM-hypertension (3, 6-8, 17, 27, 30) . Other studies demonstrated that cytochrome P-450 -hydroxylase expression is elevated in many tissues with hypertension [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , resulting in an increased production of 20-HETE, a potent constrictor of skeletal muscle arterioles [CITATION_4] . On the basis of those previous investigations, the goal of the present study was to evaluate the potential contribution of cytochrome P-450 -hydroxylase products (presumably 20-HETE) to the altered reactivity of skeletal muscle arterioles in normotensive rats on high-salt diet and in RRM-hypertensive rats.",
